    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nInteractive marks are in a separated .json file from the .tutor file. Which means if an user updates a tutor file, he has to update line numbers (could be many) in the .json file. That is a maintainance burden. And this is hard to automatically tested\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n#38522 will open a temporary file for `:Tutor` instead of the original one. After it, maybe Nvim can move \"expected\" contents to the `.tutor` file, on the same line as the original one. The syntax maybe like (Suggestions are welcome)\n```\nThis is wrong. <--This is right.-->\n```\nNvim will preprocess the file before opening it, to remove comments from buffer, apply extmarks based on removed comments, etc\n\nThis way could allow Nvim to restore the tutor hyperlink feature without relying on `conceal` feature (but IMO it is not important)",
